{
  "bank_id": "vocab_coach_task_type_bank_v1.2.0",
  "supersedes": "vocab_coach_task_type_bank_v1.1.0 (and v1.0.0) -- both kept in place, not deleted or overwritten",
  "scope_note_changelog": [
    {
      "version": "v1.0.0",
      "change": "Initial 22 items, 3 task-types, hedged/academic fixed phrases only."
    },
    {
      "version": "v1.1.0",
      "change": "Expanded to 56 items: added basic-level phrases, verbs, and collocations across levels."
    },
    {
      "version": "v1.2.0",
      "change": "Full revision per VOCAB_COACH_BANK_REVISION_PROMPT_V1.md audit. (7) Added a 4th task-type, 'discussion' (discuss-both-views), 17 items, side_a/side_b single-stance framings rather than dual-clause connectors. (8) Rebalanced type mix (added collocations, esp. cause_effect_problem_solution and advantages_disadvantages), rebalanced level mix (added intermediate items, previously the thinnest band), and pushed new items against the same registries the topic bank cites before falling back to curated wording. (9) Added an 'angle' field to every item in advantages_disadvantages, cause_effect_problem_solution, and discussion, so selection can draw only the single angle a one-idea PEEL micro-task actually needs. Removed 'outweigh' and 'outweighs the disadvantages' (inherently two-sided, X-outweighs-Y) and 'on the other hand' (a pure contrast connector presupposing a stated first side) from single-idea selection -- moved to a new top-level 'essay_level_only' bucket, not read by the engine's task-type selection at all. Dropped the 'further' framing from 'a further benefit is that'/'a further downside worth noting is' (both implied a prior point already made elsewhere, a mismatch for a standalone paragraph) rather than tagging them essay-level-only, since the underlying content is genuinely usable standalone once 'further' is removed. Rebalanced cause_effect_problem_solution from 15 cause/effect-language items vs. 4 solution-language items toward parity by adding problem-naming items (previously zero) and more solution-proposing items."
    }
  ],
